            "Based on the search results, here's what I found regarding NBA basketball prediction using XGBoost models with feature selection and statistics for 2024-2025:\n\n## Recent Research and Applications\n\nRecent studies have developed machine-learning approaches using game logs and player statistics from the 2023\u201324 and 2024\u201325 NBA seasons, incorporating game conditions and momentum indicators with an optimized XGBoost model using team-based train-test-validation, feature selection, and hyperparameter tuning.\n\n## Key Features and Predictors\n\nField goal percentage, defensive rebounds, and turnovers are critical factors affecting game outcomes across various stages of the game, with assists being key indicators during the first two quarters, while offensive rebounds and three-point shooting percentages become more influential as game time decreases.\n\nKey predictors include win streaks, home-court advantage, shooting efficiency, and player trades.\n\n## Model Performance\n\nThe success of AI models like neural networks and XGBoost often depends more on the quality and relevance of input features than on the complexity of the models themselves. Additionally, ensemble learning combined multiple algorithms to predict NBA win rates with high accuracy (R\u00b2 = 0.9332).\n\n## Feature Selection Methods\n\nSHAP values were used to interpret feature importance, and weight evaluates the importance of each variable based on the number of times it is used as a split point during the construction of decision trees."
